vectorData.altText: That's right! Notice that at this level, the belly of the pons ventrally and the middle cerebellar peduncles reaching posteriorly but they are not continuous with the cerebellum. If they were, it would be the caudal pons.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Many of these features are easily identifiable in MRI. In this image of the midpons, identify:
the “belly” of the pons, anteriorly
the middle cerebellar peduncles, larger and more lateral
the superior cerebellar peduncles, smaller and more medial
the fourth ventricle
